post_text:
Holiday Door Decoration Contest

Winners of the Annual Holiday Door Decorating Contest were announced Friday, December 20, 2019. Twenty doors, including few administrative offices were creatively decorated by students, with some assistance from their teachers. This year’s doors all have been decorated to reflect theme of the Holiday spirit.

December 9, 2019 at 10:44 AM ·

When a staff member sees a student being a Leader, Engaging others, showing Respect, and coming Prepared they will give a Born to Perform ticket. This ticket will be filled out by the student and can be placed in areas around the school. At the end of a given time ticket, two tickets from each grade level will be selected. Those students that were selected and the staff members that gave a Born to Perform ticket to those students will be given prizes.

post_text: AUL won an Environmental Science grant called PAPERS (Perth Amboy Partnership for Environmental Restoration Stewardship). In this grant, all students in grades 7-12 will participate in field trips and activities to promote student learning, as well as environmental stewardship.

post_text: This week, we are celebrating our Teachers. For the past eight months, they have worked tirelessly for the children that we serve, often coming in early, staying after school for individual tutoring, working through lunch setting up activities or grading papers, and all the while thinking of ways to ensure the students are ready to be successful in college or career when they leave us. Throughout the week, please take the time to thank every teacher at AUL.

post_text: AULCS 2019-2020 Lottery Applications are available now. The sooner you fill them out the better your chances of getting a spot. Those students in the middle school Automatically have a seat in our high school, so it is better to enroll in middle school. Our current 8th grade is full so if you have 7th grade student, you may want to enroll them for this year if you want them in for high school.

Big Brothers Big Sisters of Coastal & Northern New Jersey
April 25, 2018 at 3:54 PM ·

Executive Director William Salcedo participated in an event last week at the Academy For Urban Leadership Charter School in Perth Amboy, New Jersey. William and 20 role models spoke to over 100 9th grade students during an assembly. Pairs of role models also had an opportunity to speak with smaller groups of students as part of Comcast Cares Day efforts! HISPA.org Comcast #comcastcaresday #hispa #mentoringworks
